'''Barium stannate''' is an [[oxide]] of [[barium]] and [[tin]] with the [[chemical formula]] [[barium|Ba]][[tin|Sn]][[oxygen|O]]<sub>3</sub>. It is a wide [[band gap]] [[semiconductor]] with a [[Perovskite (structure)|perovskite]] [[crystal]] structure.<ref name="Preparation, structure and dielectric property of barium stannate titanate ceramics">{{cite journal|last1=Wei|first1=Xiaoyong|last2=Yao|first2=Xi|title=Preparation, structure and dielectric property of barium stannate titanate ceramics|journal=Materials Science and Engineering: B|date=February 2007|volume=137|issue=1-3|pages=184‚Äì188|doi=10.1016/j.mseb.2006.11.012}}<!--|accessdate=22 January 2016--></ref><ref name="Structural, electrical and optical properties of lanthanum-doped barium stannate">{{cite journal|last1=Luo|first1=B.C.|last2=Zhang|first2=J.|last3=Wang|first3=J.|last4=Ran|first4=P.X.|title=Structural, electrical and optical properties of lanthanum-doped barium stannate|journal=Ceramics International|date=March 2015|volume=41|issue=2|pages=2668‚Äì2672|doi=10.1016/j.ceramint.2014.10.080}}<!--|accessdate=22 January 2016--></ref><ref name="Tuning optical properties of transparent conducting barium stannate by dimensional reduction">{{cite journal|last1=Li|first1=Yuwei|last2=Zhang|first2=Lijun|last3=Ma|first3=Yanming|last4=Singh|first4=David J.|title=Tuning optical properties of transparent conducting barium stannate by dimensional reduction|journal=APL Materials|date=1 January 2015|volume=3|issue=1|pages=011102|doi=10.1063/1.4906785}}<!--|accessdate=22 January 2016--></ref>

