The '''Kaimai hydro power scheme''' is a [[hydroelectric power]] scheme on the [[Wairoa River, Bay of Plenty|Wairoa River]] in the Bay of Plenty in New Zealand. The scheme is operated by [[TrustPower]].<ref>[http://www.trustpower.co.nz/index.php?section=111 TrustPower] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110401133001/http://www.trustpower.co.nz/index.php?section=111 |date=2011-04-01 }} - Kaimai hydro power scheme</ref> It has four operational power stations, and formerly the McLaren Falls Station which was decommissioned in 1989 following the commissioning of the Ruahihi Station.
==Power stations== *McLaren Falls Station 750 kW - decommissioned *Lloyd Mandeno Station 16 MW *Ruahihi Station 20 MW *Lower Mangapapa Station 5.6 MW *Kaimai 5 Station 0.3 MW
